        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-01T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rinden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-01T16:00:00+09:00">September 1, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:01 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>358. Military situation northeast remains static. Elements Communist 3d column
                    formerly reported moving southwestwards from Hsian (ConGen 44 [<hi rend="italic">444</hi>] to Embassy<note n="87" xml:id="d344fn87">August 26, 3 p. m.,
                        repeated to the Department as telegram No. 354, not printed.</note>) have
                    returned to bases near Hsian. Communist 1st column has moved closer Changchun
                    from south presumably tighten blockade city and be in position assault should
                    defenders show definite signs weakness: One civilian, Communist 9th column,
                    Kowpangtze area, north Inchow, has moved northwards nearer Hsinmin area on
                    Mukden–South Peiping rail line. Communists reported repairing all highways in
                    Faku–Changwu–Hsinmin triangle northwest Mukden. No Communist troop movement
                    areas South Mukden.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 451; repeated Department 358, Peiping 192.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rinden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
